%% Request lifecycle: search → merge → stream → download
%% Covers the full user-visible flow from query to torrent download.
sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    actor User
    participant Dashboard as Dashboard (:7187)
    participant API as FastAPI API
    participant Orch as SearchOrchestrator
    participant Trackers as Trackers (subprocess + aiohttp)
    participant Dedup as Deduplicator
    participant Enrich as Enricher
    participant Proxy as Download Proxy (:7186)
    participant QBit as qBittorrent (:7185)

    User->>Dashboard: type query, click Search
    Dashboard->>API: POST /api/v1/search {query, category}
    API->>Orch: search(query, category)
    Orch->>Orch: create SearchMetadata(search_id)
    
    par fan-out concurrent searches
        Orch->>Trackers: _search_tracker(name) × N
        Trackers-->>Orch: List[SearchResult] per tracker
    end

    Orch->>Dedup: merge_results(all_results)
    Note over Dedup: Tier 1: infohash match<br/>Tier 2: name+size match<br/>Tier 3: Levenshtein fuzzy
    Dedup-->>Orch: List[MergedResult]

    opt metadata enabled
        Orch->>Enrich: fill best_quality, CanonicalIdentity
        Enrich-->>Orch: enriched results
    end

    Orch-->>API: SearchMetadata(completed)
    API-->>Dashboard: SearchResponse JSON

    User->>Dashboard: clicks Download on result
    Dashboard->>API: POST /api/v1/download {download_urls}
    API->>Proxy: fetch .torrent with auth cookies
    Proxy->>QBit: POST /api/v2/torrents/add
    QBit-->>Dashboard: torrent added to transfer list
